---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { base } from "../../utils/url";
---

<Layout title="Terms & Conditions – JÆCK" noindex={true} lang="en">
    <div class="pt-32 pb-20 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl font-light mb-12">
            Terms &amp; Conditions
        </h1>

        <div
            class="space-y-10 text-[var(--muted)] font-light leading-relaxed text-sm"
        >
            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 1 Scope
                </p>
                <p>
                    These General Terms and Conditions (T&amp;Cs) apply to all
                    contracts for live musical performances and related services
                    between the artist JÆCK (hereinafter "Artist") and the
                    respective client (hereinafter "Organiser"). Deviating
                    conditions of the Organiser will not be recognised unless
                    the Artist expressly agrees to them in writing.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 2 Formation of Contract
                </p>
                <p>
                    A binding contract (performance agreement) is formed upon
                    written confirmation (e-mail is sufficient) of an offer
                    prepared by the Artist by the Organiser. Options and date
                    reservations are non-binding until confirmed in writing as a
                    fixed booking.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 3 Fee, Payment Terms &amp; Expenses
                </p>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        The agreed fee is exclusive of any applicable taxes
                        (e.g. VAT, where the small-business exemption does not
                        apply).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Unless otherwise agreed, a deposit of 30&nbsp;% of the
                        total fee is due within 14 days of contract formation.
                        This deposit secures the date as a fixed booking for the
                        Organiser.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The remaining balance is to be transferred to the
                        Artist's account without deductions no later than 7 days
                        after the performance.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Travel costs, accommodation costs (if the venue is more
                        than 100&nbsp;km from the Artist's place of residence)
                        and other expenses are listed separately in the offer
                        and are borne by the Organiser.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>

            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 4 Cancellation Policy
                </p>
                <p class="mb-3">
                    If the Organiser cancels a confirmed booking, the following
                    cancellation fees apply:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                    <li>
                        Up to 90 days before the performance: forfeiture of the
                        deposit (30&nbsp;% of the fee).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        89 to 30 days before the performance: 50&nbsp;% of the
                        agreed total fee.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        29 to 14 days before the performance: 75&nbsp;% of the
                        agreed total fee.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Less than 14 days before the performance: 100&nbsp;% of
                        the agreed total fee.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    Exceptions apply in cases of genuine force majeure (see §
                    7).
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 5 Organiser Requirements (Stage &amp; Technical)
                </p>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        The Organiser shall provide an adequate, clean, and safe
                        performance area.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        For outdoor events, the stage/performance area must be
                        covered and protected from the elements (rain, direct
                        intense sunlight) to safeguard the Artist's equipment.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        A secured power connection (230&nbsp;V) must be
                        available in the immediate vicinity of the stage.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        If the performance cannot take place due to missing
                        technical or safety requirements, the Artist retains the
                        full right to the agreed fee.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>

            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 6 Catering
                </p>
                <p>
                    The Organiser shall provide the Artist (and any accompanying
                    persons/technicians) with adequate catering (a warm meal)
                    and sufficient non-alcoholic beverages free of charge for
                    the duration of their presence at the venue.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 7 Illness &amp; Force Majeure
                </p>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        If the Artist must cancel the performance due to
                        documented illness (medical certificate) or other
                        serious reasons beyond their control, the right to the
                        fee lapses.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Any deposits already paid will in this case be refunded
                        in full to the Organiser.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Any claim by the Organiser for damages is expressly
                        excluded in such cases. The Artist will however
                        endeavour, at the Organiser's request, to arrange a
                        suitable replacement.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>

            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 8 Copyright &amp; Performing Rights (AKM / GEMA)
                </p>
                <p>
                    The Organiser is solely responsible for registering the
                    event with the relevant performing rights organisation (e.g.
                    AKM in Austria, GEMA in Germany) in good time. All fees
                    arising from the public performance of copyright-protected
                    works are borne by the Organiser. The Artist will provide
                    the Organiser with a setlist in due course.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 9 Photo &amp; Audio/Video Recordings
                </p>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        Private photo and audio/video recordings by guests are
                        permitted.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Professional or commercial recordings of the performance
                        by the Organiser or third parties require the prior
                        written consent of the Artist.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The Artist reserves the right to create their own photo
                        and video material at the event for self-promotion,
                        unless the Organiser explicitly objects in advance.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>

            <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
                <p
                    class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--accent)] mb-4"
                >
                    § 10 Final Provisions
                </p>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        Amendments and additions to the contract must be made in
                        writing.
                    </li>
                    <li>Austrian law applies.</li>
                    <li>
                        The place of jurisdiction for all disputes arising from
                        this contract is Vienna.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </section>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
